properties.Title: Special Weather Statement In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: A low pressure system will track through the province of Quebec tonight and Monday. This system will produce significant snowfall amounts, strong to high winds and rain. Local snowfall amounts of 10 to 15 cm could affect higher elevations of Central Quebec and the Gaspé Peninsula from this evening through Monday morning. Southeasterly winds with gusts of 60 to 90 kilometres per hour are expected over the tip of the Gaspé Peninsula and the Lower North Shore on Monday. Meanwhile, over the tip of the Gaspé Peninsula and the Anticosti Island, precipitation will mostly fall as rain. Those areas could see from 20 to 30 millimetres of rain Monday. ### Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to QCstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #QCStorm.
